steps.description:
B1 (review fix): In `invokeSdk()` in session.ts, wrap the `for await` loop (lines 147-184) in a try/finally block, moving `clearTimeout(timeoutId)` from its current inline position (line 187) into the `finally` clause. The `exitPromise` await and exit-code check remain AFTER the try/finally, since they don't need timeout protection — the timeout only guards the streaming read. Structure becomes:
```
try {
  for await (const line of createLineReader(proc.stdout!)) {
    // ... existing parsing logic ...
  }
} finally {
  clearTimeout(timeoutId);
}
const exitCode = await exitPromise;
```
This guarantees clearTimeout is called regardless of how the loop exits (normal completion, thrown stream error, or rethrown abort), preventing cross-request interference from leaked timeouts.
